<subSubSection id="C3150AD1FF95FFDFECDE4607B528F9F6" pageId="15" pageNumber="520" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="8BB0595AFF95FFDFECDE4607B5DCFD5F" blockId="15.[151,1437,478,1583]" pageId="15" pageNumber="520">
<emphasis id="B97B8548FF95FFDFECDE4607B578FDBB" bold="true" box="[199,315,586,611]" pageId="15" pageNumber="520">Remarks.</emphasis>
<emphasis id="B97B8548FF95FFDFED5C4601B5D1FDBB" box="[325,402,588,611]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="520">Eurota</emphasis>
is a misspelling of 
<taxonomicName id="4C0F22D9FF95FFDFEE654601B7D0FDBB" authority="Herrich-Schaffer" authorityName="Herrich-Schaffer" box="[636,915,586,611]" class="Insecta" family="Arctiidae" genus="Eurata" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="15" pageNumber="520" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B97B8548FF95FFDFEE654601B689FDBB" box="[636,714,588,611]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="520">Eurata</emphasis>
Herrich-Schäffer
</taxonomicName>
, [
<number id="3DC74B7DFF95FFDFEFB04607B7ABFDBB" box="[937,1000,586,611]" pageId="15" pageNumber="520" value="1853.0">1853</number>
]; the genus is currently considered to belong to 
<taxonomicName id="4C0F22D9FF95FFDFED1E4623B5D8FD5F" box="[263,411,622,647]" class="Insecta" family="Erebidae" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="15" pageNumber="520" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subTribe" subTribe="Euchromiina">Euchromiina</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BB0595AFF95FFDFECDE46DFB0B4FCCF" blockId="15.[151,1437,478,1583]" pageId="15" pageNumber="520">
The history of 
<taxonomicName id="4C0F22D9FF95FFDFED7246D9B64BFD73" box="[363,520,658,683]" class="Insecta" family="Arctiidae" genus="Eurata" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="15" pageNumber="520" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="hilaris">
<emphasis id="B97B8548FF95FFDFED7246D9B64BFD73" box="[363,520,658,683]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="520">Eurata hilaris</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
involves the history of other names in the genus: it was proposed by 
<bibRefCitation id="EF9E24ABFF95FFDFE91146DEB1DFFD73" author="Zerny" box="[1288,1436,659,683]" pageId="15" pageNumber="520" refString="Zerny, H. (1937) Die Lepidopteren der Deutschen Gran-Chaco-Expedition 1925 / 26 mit Berucksichtigung der Sammelergebnisse von Professor Hosseus in der Sierra de Cordoba. IV. Syntomidae, Arctiidae und Dioptidae. Mitteilungen der Munchner Entomologischen Gesellschaft, 27, 11 - 16." type="journal article" year="1937">
Zerny (
<number id="3DC74B7DFF95FFDFE94346DEB1D7FD73" box="[1370,1428,659,683]" pageId="15" pageNumber="520" value="1937.0">1937</number>
)
</bibRefCitation>
for Hampson’s (
<number id="3DC74B7DFF95FFDFED5446FAB5C9FD17" box="[333,394,695,719]" pageId="15" pageNumber="520" value="1898.0">1898</number>
: 
<number id="3DC74B7DFF95FFDFED8C46FAB583FD17" box="[405,448,695,719]" pageId="15" pageNumber="520" value="288.0">288</number>
) concept of 
<taxonomicName id="4C0F22D9FF95FFDFEE5446FAB68EFD17" box="[589,717,694,719]" class="Insecta" family="Arctiidae" genus="Eurata" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="15" pageNumber="520" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="herrickii">
<emphasis id="B97B8548FF95FFDFEE5446FAB68EFD17" box="[589,717,694,719]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="520">E. herrickii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, a misspelling of 
<taxonomicName id="4C0F22D9FF95FFDFEF8E46FAB0ECFD17" authority="Butler, 1876" authorityName="Butler" authorityYear="1876" box="[919,1199,694,719]" class="Insecta" family="Arctiidae" genus="Eurata" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="15" pageNumber="520" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="herrichii">
<emphasis id="B97B8548FF95FFDFEF8E46FAB05BFD17" box="[919,1048,694,719]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="520">E. herrichii</emphasis>
Butler, 
<number id="3DC74B7DFF95FFDFE86D46FBB0ECFD17" box="[1140,1199,694,719]" pageId="15" pageNumber="520" value="1876.0">1876</number>
</taxonomicName>
. Hence, according to 
<bibRefCitation id="EF9E24ABFF95FFDFEC8E4696B56EFD2B" author="Zerny" box="[151,301,731,755]" pageId="15" pageNumber="520" refString="Zerny, H. (1937) Die Lepidopteren der Deutschen Gran-Chaco-Expedition 1925 / 26 mit Berucksichtigung der Sammelergebnisse von Professor Hosseus in der Sierra de Cordoba. IV. Syntomidae, Arctiidae und Dioptidae. Mitteilungen der Munchner Entomologischen Gesellschaft, 27, 11 - 16." type="journal article" year="1937">
Zerny (
<number id="3DC74B7DFF95FFDFECF14696B567FD2B" box="[232,292,731,755]" pageId="15" pageNumber="520" value="1937.0">1937</number>
)
</bibRefCitation>
, 
<taxonomicName id="4C0F22D9FF95FFDFED214691B5FBFD2B" box="[312,440,730,755]" class="Insecta" family="Arctiidae" genus="Eurata" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="15" pageNumber="520" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="herrickii">
<emphasis id="B97B8548FF95FFDFED214691B5FBFD2B" box="[312,440,730,755]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="520">E. herrickii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is both a misspelling and a misidentification of 
<emphasis id="B97B8548FF95FFDFEFD44691B016FD2B" box="[973,1109,730,755]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="520">
<taxonomicName id="4C0F22D9FF95FFDFEFD44691B011FD2B" box="[973,1106,730,755]" class="Insecta" family="Arctiidae" genus="Eurata" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="15" pageNumber="520" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="herrichii">E. herrichii</taxonomicName>
.
</emphasis>
The latter, on the other hand, was proposed by 
<bibRefCitation id="EF9E24ABFF95FFDFED4346B3B5BDFCCF" author="Butler" box="[346,510,766,791]" pageId="15" pageNumber="520" refString="Butler, A. G. (1876 a) Notes on the Lepidoptera of the family Zygaenidae, with descriptions of new genera and species. Journal of the Linnean Society (Zoology), 12 (60 - 62), 342 - 407." type="journal article" year="1876" yearSuffix="a">
Butler (
<number id="3DC74B7DFF95FFDFEDB646B3B5AAFCCF" box="[431,489,766,791]" pageId="15" pageNumber="520" value="1876.0">1876</number>
a)
</bibRefCitation>
for Herrich-Schäffer’s (
<number id="3DC74B7DFF95FFDFEF1546B3B705FCCF" box="[780,838,766,791]" pageId="15" pageNumber="520" value="1854.0">1854</number>
) concept of 
<taxonomicName id="4C0F22D9FF95FFDFEFCA46B2B0B0FCCF" authority="Perty, 1833" authorityName="Perty" authorityYear="1833" box="[979,1267,767,791]" class="Insecta" family="Thyrididae" genus="Glaucopis" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="15" pageNumber="520" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="sericaria">
<emphasis id="B97B8548FF95FFDFEFCA46B2B014FCCE" box="[979,1111,767,790]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="520">E. sericaria</emphasis>
(Perty, 
<number id="3DC74B7DFF95FFDFE8B746B2B0A9FCCF" box="[1198,1258,767,791]" pageId="15" pageNumber="520" value="1833.0">1833</number>
)
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BB0595AFF95FFDFECDE476FB05DFC5B" blockId="15.[151,1437,478,1583]" pageId="15" pageNumber="520">
The idea that 
<taxonomicName id="4C0F22D9FF95FFDFED7D4769B5A9FCE3" box="[356,490,804,827]" class="Insecta" family="Thyrididae" genus="Glaucopis" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="15" pageNumber="520" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="sericaria">
<emphasis id="B97B8548FF95FFDFED7D4769B5A9FCE3" box="[356,490,804,827]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="520">E. sericaria</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="4C0F22D9FF95FFDFEE3A4769B6E6FCE3" box="[547,677,802,827]" class="Insecta" family="Arctiidae" genus="Eurata" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="15" pageNumber="520" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="herrichii">
<emphasis id="B97B8548FF95FFDFEE3A4769B6E6FCE3" box="[547,677,802,827]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="520">E. herrichii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
are distinct species was widely accepted until the article by 
<bibRefCitation id="EF9E24ABFF95FFDFE940476EB4A0FC87" author="Zerny" pageId="15" pageNumber="520" refString="Zerny, H. (1937) Die Lepidopteren der Deutschen Gran-Chaco-Expedition 1925 / 26 mit Berucksichtigung der Sammelergebnisse von Professor Hosseus in der Sierra de Cordoba. IV. Syntomidae, Arctiidae und Dioptidae. Mitteilungen der Munchner Entomologischen Gesellschaft, 27, 11 - 16." type="journal article" year="1937">
Zerny (
<number id="3DC74B7DFF95FFDFEC86470AB498FC87" box="[159,219,839,863]" pageId="15" pageNumber="520" value="1937.0">1937</number>
)
</bibRefCitation>
, who was of the opinion not only that Hampson’s specimen was a different species, but also that the true concept of 
<taxonomicName id="4C0F22D9FF95FFDFED0A4721B5D7FC5B" box="[275,404,874,899]" class="Insecta" family="Arctiidae" genus="Eurata" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="15" pageNumber="520" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="herrichii">
<emphasis id="B97B8548FF95FFDFED0A4721B5D7FC5B" box="[275,404,874,899]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="520">E. herrichii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is, in fact, a junior synonym of 
<taxonomicName id="4C0F22D9FF95FFDFEEE34721B059FC5B" authority="Perty, 1833" authorityName="Perty" authorityYear="1833" box="[762,1050,875,899]" class="Insecta" family="Thyrididae" genus="Glaucopis" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="15" pageNumber="520" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="sericaria">
<emphasis id="B97B8548FF95FFDFEEE34721B73DFC5B" box="[762,894,876,899]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="520">E. sericaria</emphasis>
(Perty, 
<number id="3DC74B7DFF95FFDFEFCF4726B051FC5B" box="[982,1042,875,899]" pageId="15" pageNumber="520" value="1833.0">1833</number>
)
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BB0595AFF95FFDFECDE47C2B52EFBEF" blockId="15.[151,1437,478,1583]" pageId="15" pageNumber="520">
<taxonomicName id="4C0F22D9FF95FFDFECDE47C2B5C7FC7F" box="[199,388,910,935]" class="Insecta" family="Arctiidae" genus="Eurata" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="15" pageNumber="520" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="herrichii">
<emphasis id="B97B8548FF95FFDFECDE47C2B5C7FC7F" box="[199,388,910,935]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="520">Eurata herrichii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
was described from an undetermined number of specimens from the Kaden collection, currently deposited at the 
<collectionCode id="ED1EC19FFF95FFDFEDD147FEB5B9FC12" box="[456,506,947,970]" httpUri="http://grbio.org/cool/z2y8-2jfr" name="Russian Academy of Sciences, Zoological Institute, Zoological Museum" pageId="15" pageNumber="520">ZIN</collectionCode>
. Only one was found by the first author, and the drawing provided by Herrich- Schäffer (
<number id="3DC74B7DFF95FFDFED13479BB507FC37" box="[266,324,982,1007]" pageId="15" pageNumber="520" value="1854.0">1854</number>
) matches it perfectly. The 
<typeStatus id="54B4E7F8FF95FFDFEE95479AB683FC37" box="[652,704,983,1007]" pageId="15" pageNumber="520">type</typeStatus>
(s) of 
<taxonomicName id="4C0F22D9FF95FFDFEF13479AB789FC36" box="[778,970,983,1006]" class="Insecta" family="Arctiidae" genus="Eurata" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="15" pageNumber="520" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="sericaria">
<emphasis id="B97B8548FF95FFDFEF13479AB789FC36" box="[778,970,983,1006]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="520">Eurata sericaria</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, on the other hand, is (are) lost (Axel Hausmann, personal communication), and no collection visited by the first author has specimens exactly matching Perty’s illustration.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BB0595AFF95FFDFECDE400FB021FA1B" blockId="15.[151,1437,478,1583]" pageId="15" pageNumber="520">
The 
<typeStatus id="54B4E7F8FF95FFDFECE3400EB569FB83" box="[250,298,1091,1115]" pageId="15" pageNumber="520">type</typeStatus>
series of 
<taxonomicName id="4C0F22D9FF95FFDFED8E4009B643FB83" box="[407,512,1090,1115]" class="Insecta" family="Arctiidae" genus="Eurata" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="15" pageNumber="520" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="hilaris">
<emphasis id="B97B8548FF95FFDFED8E4009B643FB83" box="[407,512,1090,1115]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="520">E. hilaris</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is composed by all specimens mentioned in its original description, directly or by bibliographic evidence (
<collectionCode id="ED1EC19FFF95FFDFEDB3402AB5B3FBA7" box="[426,496,1127,1151]" pageId="15" pageNumber="520">ICZN</collectionCode>
, article 72.4.1). 
<bibRefCitation id="EF9E24ABFF95FFDFEEB4402AB700FBA7" author="Zerny" box="[685,835,1127,1151]" pageId="15" pageNumber="520" refString="Zerny, H. (1937) Die Lepidopteren der Deutschen Gran-Chaco-Expedition 1925 / 26 mit Berucksichtigung der Sammelergebnisse von Professor Hosseus in der Sierra de Cordoba. IV. Syntomidae, Arctiidae und Dioptidae. Mitteilungen der Munchner Entomologischen Gesellschaft, 27, 11 - 16." type="journal article" year="1937">
Zerny (
<number id="3DC74B7DFF95FFDFEF18402AB77FFBA7" box="[769,828,1127,1151]" pageId="15" pageNumber="520" value="1937.0">1937</number>
)
</bibRefCitation>
mentioned one specimen collected by Lindner, plus those mentioned by 
<bibRefCitation id="EF9E24ABFF95FFDFED9B40C6B601FB7B" author="Hampson" box="[386,578,1163,1187]" pageId="15" pageNumber="520" refString="Hampson, G. F. (1898) Catalogue of the Lepidoptera Phalaenae in the British Museum, vol. I: Catalogue of the Syntomidae in the collection of the British Museum. Printed by the order of the Trustees of the British Museum, London, 559 pp." type="book" year="1898">
Hampson (
<number id="3DC74B7DFF95FFDFEE1940C6B679FB7B" box="[512,570,1163,1187]" pageId="15" pageNumber="520" value="1898.0">1898</number>
)
</bibRefCitation>
and 
<bibRefCitation id="EF9E24ABFF95FFDFEE6740C7B75AFB7B" author="Orfila" box="[638,793,1162,1187]" pageId="15" pageNumber="520" refString="Orfila, R. N. (1931) Estudios de Lepidopterologia Argentina I. El genero Eurota Walker. Revista de la Sociedad Entomologica Argentina, 3, 185 - 202." type="journal article" year="1931">
Orfila (
<number id="3DC74B7DFF95FFDFEECD40C6B753FB7B" box="[724,784,1163,1187]" pageId="15" pageNumber="520" value="1931.0">1931</number>
)
</bibRefCitation>
. Hence, the 
<typeStatus id="54B4E7F8FF95FFDFEFB240C6B798FB7B" box="[939,987,1163,1187]" pageId="15" pageNumber="520">type</typeStatus>
series is composed of all of them: the single specimen collected by Lindner, the single one misidentified by 
<bibRefCitation id="EF9E24ABFF95FFDFEFA940E2B033FB1F" author="Hampson" box="[944,1136,1199,1223]" pageId="15" pageNumber="520" refString="Hampson, G. F. (1898) Catalogue of the Lepidoptera Phalaenae in the British Museum, vol. I: Catalogue of the Syntomidae in the collection of the British Museum. Printed by the order of the Trustees of the British Museum, London, 559 pp." type="book" year="1898">
Hampson (
<number id="3DC74B7DFF95FFDFE83540E2B02BFB1F" box="[1068,1128,1199,1223]" pageId="15" pageNumber="520" value="1898.0">1898</number>
)
</bibRefCitation>
, plus the seven mentioned by 
<bibRefCitation id="EF9E24ABFF95FFDFECA3409FB50CFB33" author="Orfila" box="[186,335,1234,1259]" pageId="15" pageNumber="520" refString="Orfila, R. N. (1931) Estudios de Lepidopterologia Argentina I. El genero Eurota Walker. Revista de la Sociedad Entomologica Argentina, 3, 185 - 202." type="journal article" year="1931">
Orfila (
<number id="3DC74B7DFF95FFDFED14409EB504FB33" box="[269,327,1235,1259]" pageId="15" pageNumber="520" value="1931.0">1931</number>
)
</bibRefCitation>
from different Argentinian collections (four from Mus. Nac. Hist Nat., two from Col. Lab. Zool., Facultad de Ciencias Exactas, Físicas y Naturales de Buenos Aires, and one from Col. Breyer, according to Orfila). The 
<collectionCode id="ED1EC19FFF95FFDFECD34156B55DFAEA" box="[202,286,1307,1330]" pageId="15" pageNumber="520">BMNH</collectionCode>
has two specimens from Goya, one with only this information on the label, the other, here considered the 
<typeStatus id="54B4E7F8FF95FFDFECD94172B554FA8F" box="[192,279,1343,1367]" pageId="15" pageNumber="520">syntype</typeStatus>
mentioned by 
<bibRefCitation id="EF9E24ABFF95FFDFEDA74172B63FFA8F" author="Hampson" box="[446,636,1343,1367]" pageId="15" pageNumber="520" refString="Hampson, G. F. (1898) Catalogue of the Lepidoptera Phalaenae in the British Museum, vol. I: Catalogue of the Syntomidae in the collection of the British Museum. Printed by the order of the Trustees of the British Museum, London, 559 pp." type="book" year="1898">
Hampson (
<number id="3DC74B7DFF95FFDFEE214172B637FA8F" box="[568,628,1343,1367]" pageId="15" pageNumber="520" value="1898.0">1898</number>
)
</bibRefCitation>
, with the information “Goya, 
<collectingCountry id="F31819CAFF95FFDFEFD54173B050FA8F" box="[972,1043,1342,1367]" name="Brazil" pageId="15" pageNumber="520">Brazil</collectingCountry>
, Perrens”. The mention to 
<collectingCountry id="F31819CAFF95FFDFE9274173B1C1FA8F" box="[1342,1410,1342,1367]" name="Brazil" pageId="15" pageNumber="520">Brazil</collectingCountry>
is erroneous, as this city is in the Argentinian province of Corrientes, close to the Brazilian border. The Argentinian collections could not be examined. The 
<typeStatus id="54B4E7F8FF95FFDFEE7B41CAB6D1FA47" box="[610,658,1415,1439]" pageId="15" pageNumber="520">type</typeStatus>
status of Orfila’s specimens must be carefully evaluated, given that due to the circumstances of the description of 
<taxonomicName id="4C0F22D9FF95FFDFEE8241E1B740FA1B" box="[667,771,1450,1475]" class="Insecta" family="Arctiidae" genus="Eurata" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="15" pageNumber="520" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="hilaris">
<emphasis id="B97B8548FF95FFDFEE8241E1B740FA1B" box="[667,771,1450,1475]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="520">E. hilaris</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, they will not have 
<typeStatus id="54B4E7F8FF95FFDFEFFB41E6B051FA1B" box="[994,1042,1451,1475]" pageId="15" pageNumber="520">type</typeStatus>
labels.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BB0595AFF95FFDFECDE4182B528F9F6" blockId="15.[151,1437,478,1583]" pageId="15" pageNumber="520">
Because all these taxonomic changes were proposed without examination of the 
<typeStatus id="54B4E7F8FF95FFDFE8914182B085FA3F" box="[1160,1222,1487,1511]" pageId="15" pageNumber="520">types</typeStatus>
, but only through drawings and descriptions, the validity of all these names must be reevaluated, which should be done in a full revision of 
<taxonomicName id="4C0F22D9FF95FFDFED0F425AB527F9F6" box="[278,356,1559,1582]" class="Insecta" family="Arctiidae" genus="Eurata" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="15" pageNumber="520" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B97B8548FF95FFDFED0F425AB527F9F6" box="[278,356,1559,1582]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="520">Eurata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
